---
import RedWhitePageLayout from "../../../layouts/RedWhitePageLayout.astro";
import H1 from "../../../components/ui/H1.astro";
---

<RedWhitePageLayout title="S.R.T.P. - Sinthome" useInfoLayout={true}>
      <H1 className="text-red-600">S.R.T.P.</H1>

      <div class="space-y-8 max-w-4xl">
        <!-- Overview -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">Interrogating praxis, until it unveils the future.</h2>
          <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <p class="text-gray-700 italic text-center mb-2">
              "Die Philosophen haben die Welt nur verschieden interpretiert; es kommt aber darauf an, sie zu verändern."
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-center">
              —— Karl Marx
            </p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            There is no clear path that leads theoretical critique to social praxis. Born from this rupture between theory and praxis, Sinthome Revolutionary Theory Practice (S.R.T.P.) is such a special yet indispensable program that formulates the guidelines for Sinthome's social praxis.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            By hosting weekly lectures and seminars, S.R.T.P. harbors a self-reflexive intellectual community that facilitates the necessary circulation between theoretical critique and social praxis.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Program Structure -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-6">Program Structure</h2>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-600 mb-3">Weekly Seminars</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Regular intellectual gatherings focusing on critical theory, philosophy, and their practical applications in contemporary social challenges.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-600 mb-3">Research Groups</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Small collaborative groups working on specific theoretical questions with direct relevance to social practice and community organizing.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-600 mb-3">Public Lectures</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Monthly public lectures featuring scholars, activists, and practitioners who embody the integration of theory and practice.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-600 mb-3">Praxis Projects</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Hands-on initiatives that apply theoretical insights to real-world community problems, bridging the gap between ideas and action.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Focus Areas -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">Areas of Focus</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-red-600 mr-2 mt-1">•</span>
              <div>
                <strong class="text-black">Critical Theory & Social Practice:</strong>
                <span class="text-gray-700"> Exploring how theoretical frameworks can inform and transform social action</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-red-600 mr-2 mt-1">•</span>
              <div>
                <strong class="text-black">Political Economy:</strong>
                <span class="text-gray-700"> Understanding contemporary capitalism and exploring alternative economic models</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-red-600 mr-2 mt-1">•</span>
              <div>
                <strong class="text-black">Technology & Society:</strong>
                <span class="text-gray-700"> Critical analysis of technology's role in social transformation and liberation</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-red-600 mr-2 mt-1">•</span>
              <div>
                <strong class="text-black">Community Organizing:</strong>
                <span class="text-gray-700"> Practical strategies for building solidarity and collective action</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Join Us -->
        <section class="mt-12 p-8 bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg text-center">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">Join SRTP</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            Become part of our intellectual community dedicated to bridging theory and practice for social transformation.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/redwhite/contact"
            class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-red-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-red-700 transition-colors"
          >
            Get Involved
          </a>
        </section>
      </div>
</RedWhitePageLayout>